LanguageData.ARA_InteractiveEggSac_Start.label: First-born Arachnidae egg sac
LanguageData.ARA_InteractiveEggSac_Start.description: A fragile, flammable, slimy sac, it is the first egg laid here by the Empress Arachne. It contains nutrients and genetic material to raise new insects, which can be activated by contact with the Empress Arachne.\n\nFirst-born egg sacs can withstand extreme weather and hatch very quickly, but only a limited number of insect families can hatch them.
LanguageData.ARA_InteractiveEggSac_Queen.label: Arachne empress egg sac
LanguageData.ARA_InteractiveEggSac_Queen.description: A super-large egg sac for hatching Empress Arachne species.The epidermis is hard enough to rival that of a fortress, and the inside is filled with genetic material and nutrients needed to hatch a gigantic being unlike any other on this planet.
